23/02/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- President Branko Crvenkovski intends to engage actively in co-ordinating and implementing key judicial reforms in his country, it was announced Tuesday (22 February).
Crvenkovski met with top judicial officials, who agreed that restructuring the judiciary is a state priority that must not be delayed.
The reform is a key condition for Euro-Atlantic integration.
(Makfax, A1 TV - 22/02/05)
